Citation.sTitle: Molar Excess Volumes and Excess Isentropic Compressibilities of {2-Methylaniline (i) + Benzene (j) + Methylbenzene}, {2-Methylaniline (i) + Benzene (j) + 1,2-Dimethylbenzene (k)}, and {2-Methylaniline (i) + Benzene (j) + 1,4-Dimethylbenzene (k)} at T = 308.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Molar excess volumes, VEijk, and speeds of sound, Uijk, of {2-methylaniline (i) + benzene (j) + methylbenzene (k)}, {2-methylaniline (i) + benzene (j) + 1,2-dimethylbenzene (k)}, and {2-methylaniline (i) + benzene (j) + 1,4-dimethylbenzene (k)} have been measured as a function of composition at a temperature of 308.15 K. The observed speeds of sound data have been utilized to determine excess isentropic compressibilities, ?S ijkE of ternaries (i + j + k).
